This paper discusses a social learning model that describes belief dynamics over social networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of social networks and information retrieval (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also extends the non-Bayesian social learning model, which involves the use of imperfect signal knowledge, and proposes strategies for improving social learning processes and results, which are topics that fall under the scope of machine learning (cs.LG), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
